   "tid": "T34",
   "prompt": "Calculate the diffusion path of a Cu adatom moving from an fcc hollow to an hcp hollow site on a Cu FCC(111) surface using NEB. Use 5 images with IDPP interpolation. Print the energy barrier (difference between maximum energy and initial energy).",
   "category": "neb",
   "difficulty": "L3",
   "tests_api": "ase.mep.NEB, neb.interpolate(method='idpp')",
   "code": "from ase.build import fcc111, add_adsorbate\nfrom ase.calculators.emt import EMT\nfrom ase.mep import NEB\nfrom ase.optimize import BFGS\n\n# Create Cu(111) slab\nslab = fcc111('Cu', size=(3, 3, 4), vacuum=10.0)\nslab.calc = EMT()\n\n# Optimize clean slab\nBFGS(slab).run(fmax=0.05)\n\n# Create initial state (fcc hollow)\ninitial = slab.copy()\nadd_adsorbate(initial, 'Cu', height=1.5, position='fcc')\ninitial.calc = EMT()\nBFGS(initial).run(fmax=0.05)\n\n# Create final state (hcp hollow)\nfinal = slab.copy()\nadd_adsorbate(final, 'Cu', height=1.5, position='hcp')\nfinal.calc = EMT()\nBFGS(final).run(fmax=0.05)\n\n# Create NEB images\nimages = [initial] + [initial.copy() for _ in range(5)] + [final]\nneb = NEB(images)\nneb.interpolate(method='idpp')\n\n# Set calculators for intermediate images\nfor image in images[1:-1]:\n    image.calc = EMT()\n\n# Run NEB optimization\nBFGS(neb).run(fmax=0.05)\n\n# Calculate energy barrier\nenergies = [image.get_potential_energy() for image in images]\nbarrier = max(energies) - energies[0]\nprint(f\"Energy barrier: {barrier:.3f} eV\")\n",
